           MODULE=xautolock
         VERSION=2.2
          SOURCE=$MODULE-$VERSION.tgz
      SOURCE_URL=https://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/X11/screensavers/
        WEB_SITE=http://freshmeat.net/projects/xautolock/
      SOURCE_VFY=sha256:11f0275175634e6db756e96f5713ec91b8b1c41f8663df54e8a5d27dc71c4da2
         ENTERED=20011113
         UPDATED=20160529
           SHORT="An automatic X screen-locker/screen-saver"

cat << EOF
Xautolock monitors console activity under the X window system, and fires
up a program of your choice if nothing happens during a user configurable
period of time. You can use this to automatically start up a screen locker
in case you tend to forget to do so manually before having a coffee break.
EOF
